The RDS Proxy is already fixing the latency. We proved DB connection time dropped from about 5.5 seconds to around 158 ms. The remaining 502 is because the Proxy can authenticate the Lambda, but the Proxy itself cannot authenticate to Aurora. The Proxy logs explicitly say DefaultAuthScheme must be IAM_AUTH. So the fix is to configure end to end IAM auth on the Proxy and give the Proxy role rds-db:connect permission for pgsi_ans00315015.
Show more lines

Bottom line: do not remove RDS Proxy. Update the Proxy to end to end IAM auth.
